reviews_data.owner_answer:
Savannah, 

Thank you for your honest review. We only allow 50% on select drinks because the sugar comes from the fruit syrup/purées. If our staff did not explain this clearly to you we apologize for that. In terms of sweetness level, there is a 75%, which is between 50% and 100%. 75% would cut the sweetness of the drink so it’s not so sweet. We have an option for sugar level because our milk teas can be made to a sugar level below 50%. This is because we use a homemade sugar syrup. The reason it’s advertised is because we have to have a way to let customers know. Typically, the explanation of why we can’t offer below 50% on fruit teas is enough but sometimes the message gets lost in translation. We hope you choose to visit again and hope next time you try out 75% sweet! 

Regards, 
- B&K Management

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Savannah, 

Thank you for your honest review. We only allow 50% on select drinks because the sugar comes from the fruit syrup/purées. If our staff did not explain this clearly to you we apologize for that. In terms of sweetness level, there is a 75%, which is between 50% and 100%. 75% would cut the sweetness of the drink so it’s not so sweet. We have an option for sugar level because our milk teas can be made to a sugar level below 50%. This is because we use a homemade sugar syrup. The reason it’s advertised is because we have to have a way to let customers know. Typically, the explanation of why we can’t offer below 50% on fruit teas is enough but sometimes the message gets lost in translation. We hope you choose to visit again and hope next time you try out 75% sweet! 

Regards, 
- B&K Management
